<br>
For me: I was raised in a church going home.  They sprinkled me as a baby (though I do not call that baptism).  And I was taught for as long as I can remember about God and Jesus and the Bible.  Every night my parents would make me say my prayers before going to bed.  I've loved God my whole life, I can't remember a time ever that I didn't believe in Him or didn't love Him.<br>
<br>
Yet growing up in my church, I was under the impression by them that I was a Christian because I was physically born into a church going family.  If your name was on the membership role of a church - you were a Christian.<br>
<br>
When I was 12, I went to my first church camp/retreat ever.  It was very different than anything I had ever experienced before.  And for the first time, I was told that no one could physically be born a Christian.  That no matter what kind of family we are born into, we are still born sinners in need of God's grace and that we have to willfully choose God on our own accord and can not rely on our parents faith.  Then they gave us the opportunity to accept Jesus into our lives to be our Lord and Savior and I jumped at the chance.  Not because I was afraid of going to hell but because I'd love Jesus all my life and now that I knew what He wanted me to do to show Him my love - by accepting His grace and sacrifice and making Him my Lord and Savior.<br>
<br>
I was 12, I really didn't understand the concept of hell yet, which is really why my decision wasn't based out of fear.<br>
<br>
As for why I choose Christ today - He has literally proved Himself to me to be real so many times in so many ways that there is no doubt in my mind that He exists and is who He says He is.  Like a song we sometimes sing in church says, &quot;Seeking You as a precious jewel, Lord to give up I'd be a fool.&quot;  I'd be a fool to give up now, after I know Him to be real.  But because my love for Him has never changed and if anything has gotten stronger over the years.  He's my Daddy and I'll love Him forever. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">**********************************************<br>
